  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Peter Lang Verlag in 2019, Hatice Ayd\u0131n's <em>Digital Marketing Applications</em> occupies a modest but tangible footprint in the digital marketing literature. The book circulates through commercial retail channels and holds library placements at four institutions, with early scholarly citations beginning to accumulate\u2014signs of a work finding its footing as both a teaching resource and a reference point for researchers.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The strongest measurable signal surrounding this book is its commercial availability: presence on major retail platforms indicates that the work has been positioned and distributed for a broad audience reaching well beyond institutional library catalogs. This commercial linkage, combined with holdings at four libraries catalogued under the subjects of marketing, internet marketing, and social media, suggests the book functions as an accessible entry point into the applied dimensions of digital marketing\u2014a profile consistent with a text designed to bridge academic instruction and professional practice.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">In pedagogical terms, the book has attracted at least one adoption signal through the Open Textbook Library ecosystem, where it appears in connection with foundational digital marketing curricula. While the current library footprint remains limited to four holdings, this combination of open educational resource adjacency and retail availability positions the work as a potential pedagogical anchor in courses spanning business, marketing, and applied computer science\u2014fields that map closely to the book's own disciplinary coordinates.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Scholarly uptake, while still early-stage, has begun to materialize. Three citing works have been recorded, with two appearing in 2023 and one in 2025, suggesting a modest but continued relevance rather than a single burst of attention. The citing works are geographically distributed across Malaysia and India, and originate from institutions including the National University of Malaysia, Alagappa University, and Jamia Millia Islamia. The work has been drawn upon in a bibliometric analysis of digital marketing research trends published in the <em>International Journal of Marketing Communication and New Media</em>, in a dissertation on multimodal genre analysis of online product information, and in a book chapter undertaking bibliometric analysis of search engine optimization strategies. This diversity of citing contexts\u2014spanning literature reviews, linguistic analysis, and strategic decision-making\u2014points to the book's utility as a foundational reference across applied and methodological inquiries in the field.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, <em>Digital Marketing Applications</em> sits at the 24th percentile for scholarly citation impact among comparable works, a figure that honestly reflects its early-stage citation profile while leaving room for continued uptake. The book's trajectory\u2014slow initial diffusion, followed by renewed citing activity beginning four years after publication\u2014is not uncommon for applied academic texts in rapidly evolving fields. As digital marketing continues to mature as a scholarly discipline, works that document its applied foundations may find sustained, if incremental, relevance among researchers, educators, and graduate students seeking orienting references.</p>",
